Step 3: Restore with KMS Key
When restoring in the destination account, you can either:
Option A: Use the source account's KMS key
aws rds restore-db-instance-from-db-snapshot \
    --db-instance-identifier my-restored-db \
    --db-snapshot-identifier arn:aws:rds:region:source-account-id:snapshot:snapshot-name \
    --kms-key-id arn:aws:kms:region:source-account-id:key/key-id

Option B: Re-encrypt with destination account's KMS key
aws rds restore-db-instance-from-db-snapshot \
    --db-instance-identifier my-restored-db \
    --db-snapshot-identifier arn:aws:rds:region:source-account-id:snapshot:snapshot-name \
    --kms-key-id arn:aws:kms:region:destination-account-id:key/destination-key-id

Quick Tip
If you want the destination account to fully own the database, use Option B (re-encrypt with their own KMS key). This removes the dependency on the source account's key.
